    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission Response (defaults applied)
    K8sAPI-->>User: SparkApplication created

    Note over Controller,Executor: State: New → Submitted → Running

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch SparkApplication CRs<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: SparkApplication event (New)
    Controller->>SparkSubmit: Submit Spark application (in-process)
    SparkSubmit->>K8sAPI: Create Driver Pod<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate--v1-pod<br/>HTTPS/443→9443 TLS<br/>Auth: API Server CA
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Pod mutated (config injected)
    K8sAPI-->>SparkSubmit: Driver Pod created

    Driver->>K8sAPI: Create Executor Pods<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate--v1-pod<br/>HTTPS/443→9443 TLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Executor Pods mutated
    K8sAPI-->>Driver: Executor Pods created

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Web UI Service (4040/TCP)<br/>Create Ingress (80/TCP)

    Note over Controller,Executor: State: Running → Completed/Failed

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update SparkApplication status<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

